item.text:
How I created a Beautiful Vocal Reverb using a Guitar Amp - Interview
Double Shadows came in to the studio for a quick recording of "Fingertips". I remembered an old recorded of St. Vincent at the Lake Fever Sessions where they used a spring like reverb for her vocal. Inspired by this faint memory, I grabbed the Princeton Reverb off the shelf and played a headphone feed of just the vocal signal into this amp.
YouTube | Creative Sound Lab

item.text:
Thomas Heatherwick, Architecture's Showman
Stephen Ross, the seventy-seven-year-old billionaire property developer and the owner of the Miami Dolphins, has a winningly informal, old-school conversational style. On a recent morning in Manhattan, he spoke of the moment, several years ago, when he decided that the plaza of one of his projects, Hudson Yards-a Doha-like cluster of towers on Manhattan's West Side-needed a magnificent object at its center.
